  <!--
    Name and summary:
    https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-app-authors/metainfo-guidelines/#name-and-summary
  -->
  <name>K’uychi</name>
  <summary>Generate color palettes with all their shades and copy their hex codes</summary>

  <!--
    Developer name:
    https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-app-authors/metainfo-guidelines/#developer-name
  -->
  <developer id="ar.liber.nyx">
    <name translatable="no">[nyx]</name>
  </developer>

  <!-- Description: https://docs.flathub.org/docs/for-app-authors/metainfo-guidelines/#description -->
  <description>
    <p>
      Have you ever found yourself searching for the perfect shade of color for your design or
      development project, only to end up with 50 tabs open in your browser? With K’uychi, those
      days are over!
    </p>

    <p>
      K’uychi (which means “rainbow” in Quechua) is your ideal tool for quickly and easily building
      harmonious color palettes. Simply choose a base color, and K’uychi will automatically generate
      a series of shades (lighter and darker tones) so you have a complete range at your fingertips.
    </p>

    <p>
      Forget about guesswork. Each shade generated can be instantly copied in its hexadecimal
      format, ready to be pasted into your CSS code, design editor, or wherever you need it.
      Designed with usability and GNOME/Libadwaita aesthetics in mind, K’uychi is the perfect
      companion for designers, developers, and anyone looking for precision and efficiency in color
      management.
    </p>

    <p>
      Simplify your color workflow and give your projects that rainbow touch they deserve with
      K’uychi!
    </p>
  </description>

  <launchable type="desktop-id">@launchable@</launchable>

